m828HubRiFTolState.name: m828HubRiFTolState
m828HubRiFTolState.description: This parameter controls the Ring In (RI) fault tolerance behavior. The default value for this parameter is the same setting as is present for m828HubRiFTolSw. SETTING this parameter overrides the value derived from m828HubRiFTolSw. Off(1) means that phantom currentis not used on the corresponding RI interface as a condition for main ring link insertion. On (2) means that phantom current is used on the corresponding RI interface as a condition for main ring link insertion. The preffered setting for this parameter is on (2).

configFLASHCount.name: configFLASHCount
configFLASHCount.description: The Quantity of FLASH installed (number of ICs).

configDRAMSize.name: configDRAMSize
configDRAMSize.description: The Quantity of DRAM installed (number of bytes).

configDRAMCount.name: configDRAMCount
configDRAMCount.description: The Quantity of DRAM installed (number of SIMMs).

configRS232Number.name: configRS232Number
configRS232Number.description: The Number of RS-232 ports in the RS-232 port table.

configRS232PortTable.name: configRS232PortTable
configRS232PortTable.description: A list of port entries. The number of entries is given by the value of configRS232Number.

configRS232PortEntry.name: configRS232PortEntry
configRS232PortEntry.description: Status and parameter values for a port.

configRS232PortIndex.name: configRS232PortIndex
configRS232PortIndex.description: A unique value for each port.

configRS232PortName.name: configRS232PortName
configRS232PortName.description: A text description of the port, i.e. COM1.

configRS232BaudRate.name: configRS232BaudRate
configRS232BaudRate.description: The baudrate at which the port is operating.

configRS232ModemStatus.name: configRS232ModemStatus
configRS232ModemStatus.description: The current status of the modem port connection.

configRS232ConnectionStatus.name: configRS232ConnectionStatus
configRS232ConnectionStatus.description: The current status of the modem data connection.

configRS232ModemConfigString.name: configRS232ModemConfigString
configRS232ModemConfigString.description: A user-configurable ASCII string used to initialize a modem on this port. If this string is set to Z, the Star-Tek Agent sends ATZ<CR> to the modem during configuration.

configRS232OutputData.name: configRS232OutputData
configRS232OutputData.description: Raw data to be sent out this port. Data can only be sent if the ConnectionStatus is connectionWait.

configRS232InputData.name: configRS232InputData
configRS232InputData.description: The response, if any, to the output data.

configRS232HardwareFlowControl.name: configRS232HardwareFlowControl
configRS232HardwareFlowControl.description: Controls the use of RTS-CTS hardware flow control during modem connections.

configMonitorMode.name: configMonitorMode
configMonitorMode.description: The mode of operation of the monitor port. The monitor port is COM2 (if present, COM1 if not).

configMonitorInput.name: configMonitorInput
configMonitorInput.description: Controls whether the monitor function will accept input.

configMonitorDiags.name: configMonitorDiags
configMonitorDiags.description: Controls whether the monitor function will produce diagnostic output.

configParseControl.name: configParseControl
configParseControl.description: Controls the degree to which frames are copied and parsed. Under high network loads this control can be used to prevent agent overload.

configBootSource.name: configBootSource
configBootSource.description: Describes where the agent is executing code from.

securityControl.name: securityControl
securityControl.description: This controls whether security is enabled or disabled.

securityMacAddressTable.name: securityMacAddressTable
securityMacAddressTable.description: A table which maintains a list of MacAddresses which are from the local ring, along with a control field which specifies whether it is allowed or disallowed access to the local ring and a counter which tracks the number of times that address has been disallowed access to the ring.

securityMacAddress.name: securityMacAddress
securityMacAddress.description: The Token Ring Mac Address for this entry.

securityStatus.name: securityStatus
securityStatus.description: Specifies whether this address is allowed or disallowed to be on the local ring.

securityLockoutCount.name: securityLockoutCount
securityLockoutCount.description: The number of times this address was disallowed on the local ring.

recoveryControl.name: recoveryControl
recoveryControl.description: This variable controls whether or not this agent will Accelerate the token-ring recovery process. Enabled by default.

recovery828Support.name: recovery828Support
recovery828Support.description: This variable controls whether this agent will perform Accelerated Recovery on model 828 devices. Disabled by default.

recoveryRetryLimit.name: recoveryRetryLimit
recoveryRetryLimit.description: This variable controls the maximum number of Accelerated Recovery events that will be attempted within recoveryRetryTimePeriod seconds of each other.

recoveryRetryTimePeriod.name: recoveryRetryTimePeriod
recoveryRetryTimePeriod.description: The number of seconds which must elapse between Recovery events in order for them to be considered non-related and non-limited.

trHistoryTable.name: trHistoryTable
trHistoryTable.description: A list of Token Ring history entries.

trHistoryEntry.name: trHistoryEntry
trHistoryEntry.description: An historical sample of Token Ring statistics on a particular Token Ring interface (on a per station basis). This sample is associated with the historyControlEntry which set up the parameters for a regular collection of these samples.

trHistoryIndex.name: trHistoryIndex
trHistoryIndex.description: The history of which this entry is a part. The history identified by a particular value of this index is the same history as identified by the same value of historyControlIndex.

trHistorySampleIndex.name: trHistorySampleIndex
trHistorySampleIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies the particular sample this entry represents among all samples associated with the same historyControlEntry. This index starts at 1 and increases by one as each new sample is taken.

trHistoryIntervalStart.name: trHistoryIntervalStart
trHistoryIntervalStart.description: The value of sysUpTime at the start of the interval over which this sample was measured. If the probe keeps track of the time of day, it should start the first sample of the history at a time such that when the next hour of the day begins, a sample is started at that instant. Note that following this rule may require the probe to delay collecting the first sample of the history, as each sample must be of the same interval. Also note that the sample which is currently being collected is not accessible in this table until the end of its interval.

trHistoryInPkts.name: trHistoryInPkts
trHistoryInPkts.description: The number of packets (including error packets) received by this station, during this sampling interval.

trHistoryOutPkts.name: trHistoryOutPkts
trHistoryOutPkts.description: The number of packets (including error packets) transmitted by this station, during this sampling interval.

trHistoryInOctets.name: trHistoryInOctets
trHistoryInOctets.description: The total number of octets of data (including those in bad packets) received on the network (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets) by this station, during this sampling interval.

trHistoryOutOctets.name: trHistoryOutOctets
trHistoryOutOctets.description: The total number of octets of data (including those in bad packets) transmitted on the network (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets) by this station, during this sampling interval.

trHistoryOutBroadcastPkts.name: trHistoryOutBroadcastPkts
trHistoryOutBroadcastPkts.description: The total number of good packets transmitted on the network that were directed to the broadcast address by this station, during this sampling interval.

trHistoryOutMulticastPkts.name: trHistoryOutMulticastPkts
trHistoryOutMulticastPkts.description: The total number of good packets transmitted on the network that were directed to a multicast address by this station, during this sampling interval. Note that this number does not include packets addressed to the broadcast address.

trHistoryClaimTokenPkts.name: trHistoryClaimTokenPkts
trHistoryClaimTokenPkts.description: The total number of Claim Token MAC packets detected by this station during this sampling interval.

trHistoryInLineErrors.name: trHistoryInLineErrors
trHistoryInLineErrors.description: The total number of line errors reported by this station in error reporting packets detected by the probe during this sampling interval.

trHistoryOutLineErrors.name: trHistoryOutLineErrors
trHistoryOutLineErrors.description: The total number of line errors reported in error reporting packets sent by the nearest active downstream neighbor of this station and detected by the probe during this sampling interval.

trHistoryInternalErrors.name: trHistoryInternalErrors
trHistoryInternalErrors.description: The total number of adapter internal errors reported by this station in error reporting packets detected by the probe during this sampling interval.

trHistoryInBurstErrors.name: trHistoryInBurstErrors
trHistoryInBurstErrors.description: The total number of burst errors reported by this station in error reporting packets detected by the probe during this sampling interval.

trHistoryOutBurstErrors.name: trHistoryOutBurstErrors
trHistoryOutBurstErrors.description: The total number of burst errors reported in error reporting packets sent by the nearest active downstream neighbor of this station and detected by the probe, during this sampling interval.

trHistoryACErrors.name: trHistoryACErrors
trHistoryACErrors.description: The total number of AC (Address Copied) errors reported in error reporting packets sent by the nearest active downstream neighbor of this station and detected by the probe during this sampling interval.

trHistoryAbortErrors.name: trHistoryAbortErrors
trHistoryAbortErrors.description: The total number of abort delimiters reported by this station in error reporting packets detected by the probe during this sampling interval.

trHistoryLostFrameErrors.name: trHistoryLostFrameErrors
trHistoryLostFrameErrors.description: The total number of lost frame errors reported by this station in error reporting packets detected by the probe during this sampling interval.

trHistoryCongestionErrors.name: trHistoryCongestionErrors
trHistoryCongestionErrors.description: The total number of receive congestion errors reported by this station in error reporting packets detected by the probe during this sampling interval.

trHistoryFrameCopiedErrors.name: trHistoryFrameCopiedErrors
trHistoryFrameCopiedErrors.description: The total number of frame copied errors reported by this station in error reporting packets detected by the probe during this sampling interval.

trHistoryFrequencyErrors.name: trHistoryFrequencyErrors
trHistoryFrequencyErrors.description: The total number of frequency errors reported by this station in error reporting packets detected by the probe during this sampling interval.

trHistoryTokenErrors.name: trHistoryTokenErrors
trHistoryTokenErrors.description: The total number of token errors reported by this station in error reporting packets detected by the probe during this sampling interval.

trHistoryInBeaconErrors.name: trHistoryInBeaconErrors
